-1 518 "1.  Basic Calculations.  We begin by experimenting with some v
ery basic calculations.  The intent is to learn some basic Maple synta
x, while observing some of the neat features of a Computer Algebra Sys
tem (CAS).  We will also review some basic concepts from arithmetic.  \+
 Perform the following calculations with Maple.  As you do these exerc
ises enter notes and comments onto your worksheet in text mode.  In pa
rticular, the author of these worksheets sometimes purposefully leaves
 off certain required Maple syntax. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 834 "The first example is in the first prob
lem below.  A CAS requires some syntaxual thing to tell it when you ar
e through giving it instructions on what you want it to do and when yo
u are ready for it to do them.  Try the first calculation just as indi
cated, look at the error message and see if you can figure out what sy
ntax is required by Maple to tell it that you are ready for it to do i
ts thing. (Place the cursor on the execution line indicated by the sym
bol [> and type in your Maple instructions, a.k.a. \"input.\")  Then, \+
compute each of the indicated arithmetic calculations.  Use parathesis
 if and where you need to.  Note the usage of operators +,-,*,/,^,!  a
nd the usage or non-usage of parentheses.   (You can always get new ex
ecution lines positioning your cursor in the worksheet and then clicki
ng on [> from the toolbar.) " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 30 "a.    6+5;                    " }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 " 6+5; " }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#
\"#6" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 12 "b.   2*3+5  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
