}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 283 95 "The program thinks 2 is
 a variable that has not been assigned a value yet so it prints it as \+
2." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 22 "4.  Prime Numbers.  A " }{TEXT 278 
12 "prime number" }{TEXT -1 38 " is an integer (greater than 1 -- why \+
" }{TEXT 258 12 "greater than" }{TEXT -1 124 " 1?) for which the only \+
(positive integer) factors are 1 and itself.  Examples of prime number
s are: 2, 13, 101, 20110771.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "The Maple command " }{TEXT 259 7 "isprime
" }{TEXT -1 58 " determines whether or not a given integer is prime.  \+
Use " }{TEXT 260 7 "isprime" }{TEXT -1 105 " it to determine whether  \+
the following numbers are prime:  29,  35,  1537,  your ss#,   10!+1, \+
 329891. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "isprime (29);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%%tr
ueG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "isprime (35);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%&fa
lseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "isprime (1537);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%&falseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 20 "isprime (522908595);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 
"6#%&falseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "isprime (10!
+1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%&falseG" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "isprime (329891);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#%%trueG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 50 "Find all of th
e prime numbers between 0 and 200.  " }{TEXT 274 4 "Note" }{TEXT -1 
63 ":  It will be helpful for you to review the information in the " }
{TEXT 263 11 "programming" }{TEXT -1 15 " worksheet on  " }{TEXT 264 
9 "for loops" }{TEXT -1 6 " and  " }{TEXT 265 13 "if statements" }
{TEXT -1 1 "." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 89 "\nfor i from 0 to 200\n do\n  if isprime (i)   \+
\n    then print(i)\n     end if;\n      end do;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
