" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 269 97 "What wa
s the common theme of the above three sets of calculations for differe
nt pairs of numbers?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 287 56 "E
ach pair was stated in the prime factors of 2,7and 11.." }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 147 "Use the Fundamental
 Theorem of Arithmetic to provide a written argument to verify the gen
eral formula that for any pair of positive integers (m,n):" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 4 "for " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 11 
"a:=m;\nb:=n;" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "mn = gcd(m
,n) * lcm(m,n);" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#/%#mnG*&%\"mG\"\"\"%\"nGF'" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 271 9 "Argument:" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT 288 66 "For any positive intergers (a,b)  a*b= gcd(a,b) tim
es the lcm(a,b)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 198 "8.   Numerical Approximations.  While Maple can perform \+
exact arithmetic, there are times when it is important or helpful to o
btain a decimal approximation for some exact answer.  For instance, th
e " }{TEXT 272 5 "solve" }{TEXT -1 66 " command can be used to find th
e \"exact\" roots of the polynomial  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p := x^3-11*x^2
-70*x+600;" "6#>%\"pG,**$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*&\"#6F)*$F'\"\"#F)!\"\"*&\"#
qF)F'F)F.\"$+'F)" }{TEXT -1 34 " .  Execute the following command:" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
43 "roots_of_p := solve(x^3-11*x^2-70*x+600,x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%+roots_of_pG6%\"\"',&#\"\"&\"\"#\"\"\"*(F)F+F*!\"\"\"
#<#F+F*F+,&F(F+*(F)F+F*F-F.F/F-" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 289 "That isn't very illuminating.  It maybe \+
hard to tell, but there are three roots.  If you change the problem sl
ightly, it may be even harder.  (For example, change the number 70 in \+
the above problem to 80 and then do the calculation!)  To display each
 root separately, execute the commands:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 43 "roots_of_p := solve(x^3
-11*x^2-80*x+600,x);" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 
12 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%+roots_of_pG6%,(*&\"\"$!\"\",&\"%4GF)*&^#
\"#!*\"\"\"\"%M[#F/\"\"#F/#F/F(F/*(\"$h$F/F(F)F*#F)F(F/#\"#6F(F/,**&\"
\"'F)F*F3F)*(F5F/F;F)F*F6F)F7F/*(^#F1F/F(F1,&*&F(F)F*F3F/*(F5F/F(F)F*F
6F)F/F/,**&F;F)F*F3F)*(F5F/F;F)F*F6F)F7F/*(^##F)F2F/F(F1F?F/F/" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
24 "r1 := Re(roots_of_p[1]);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#r1G
,&#\"#6\"\"$\"\"\"*&#F)F(F)-%#ReG6#,&*$),&\"%4G!\"\"*&^#\"#!*F)\"%M[#F
)\"\"#F)F+F)F)*&\"$h$F)F2#F4F(F)F)F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r2 := Re(roots_of_p[2]);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#r2G,&#\"#6\"\"$\"\"\"*&#F)\"\"'F)-%#ReG6#,(*$),&\"%4
G!\"\"*&^#\"#!*F)\"%M[#F)\"\"#F)#F)F(F)F5*&\"$h$F)F3#F5F(F5*(^#F(F)F(F
:,&*&F(F5F3F<F)*(F>F)F(F5F3F?F5F)F)F)F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r3 := Re(roots_of_p[3]);" }}{PARA 12 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#r3G,&#\"#6\"\"$\"\"\"*&#F)\"\"'F)-%#ReG6#,(*$),&\"%4
G!\"\"*&^#\"#!*F)\"%M[#F)\"\"#F)#F)F(F)F5*&\"$h$F)F3#F5F(F5*(^#!\"$F)F
(F:,&*&F(F5F3F<F)*(F>F)F(F5F3F?F5F)F)F)F)" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 47 "Even that isn't all that helpfu
l.  The command " }{TEXT 273 5 "evalf" }{TEXT -1 187 "  which stands f
or \"evaluate using floating point\" can be used to give a decimal app
roximation of an value.  The number of decimal places can be specified
.  Execute the following command:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "evalf(r1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$\"+<j,k8!\")" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 10 "evalf(r2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#$!+`T]#3)!\"*" }
}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "evalf(r3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 
